  "plainText": "Exclusive to:\nBarnacle Nigiri\nFood Info\n37.5\n40\n15\nMeat\nObject Info\n10 Days\nCan be Burned\n40\nCooking Info\nx1 x1 x1.0 x1\n10 sec\n30\nMiscellaneous\n\"barnaclesushi\"\n“I still seem to have misplaced my chopsticks.”\n–Wilson\n“I can still see the barnacle hiding under there.”\n–Willow\n“Is too tiny!”\n–Wolfgang\n“It's cold...”\n–Wendy\n“NUTRITION HAS BEEN PREPARED. BEGIN CONSUMPTION”\n–WX-78\n“I think I'm developing a taste for it.”\n–Wickerbottom\n“Can't say I ever saw that on a menu back home.”\n–Woodie\n“At least it's an attempt at sophistication.”\n–Maxwell\n“I hunger för möre!”\n–Wigfrid\n“Wow, fancy!”\n–Webber\n“Ah, bon! That turned out quite nicely!”\n–Warly\n“Belly stuff”\n–Wormwood\n“Can't say I've ever tasted somethin' quite like that before.”\n–Winona\n“Perhaps one of the mortals will enjoy it.”\n–Wortox\n“Glurph...”\n–Wurt\n“It's... interesting.”\n–Walter\n“All wrapped up with a little bow.”\n–Wanda\nBarnacle Nigiri is a Crock Pot recipe exclusive to Don't Starve Together introduced in Return of Them. It is made of 1 Barnacles, 1 Kelp Fronds and 1 Eggs.\nOnly Raw and Cooked Kelp Fronds are accepted. Using Dried Kelp Fronds will result in Barnacle Pita instead.\nRecipe[edit | edit source]\nExamples[edit | edit source]\nTrivia[edit | edit source]\nBarnacle Nigiri was introduced in the Troubled Waters update.\nBy TypeBy Crock Pot Value\nView or edit this template\nFood and Edible Items (by Food Type)\nVeggie\nSeeds\nMeat\nGoodies\nGeneric\nHorrible\nRoughage\nElementals\nBurnt\nRaw\nGears\nGold Dust\nBerry\nWood\nNitre\nLunar Shards\nView or edit this template\nFood and Edible Items (by Food Value)\nMeats\nFishes\nVegetables\nFruits\nMonster Food\nEggs\nDairy\nSweetener\nFrozen\nInedibles\nMagic\nFat\nSeed\nJellyfish\nBone\nFilter\nAntihistamine\nDecoration\nBug\nNo Value Food",
